.TH "pciehp_set_indicators" 9 "pciehp_set_indicators" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pciehp_set_indicators \- set attention indicator, power indicator, or both
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" pciehp_set_indicators
.BI "(struct controller *ctrl "  ","
.BI "int pwr "  ","
.BI "int attn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctrl" 12
PCIe hotplug controller
.IP "pwr" 12
one of:
PCI_EXP_SLTCTL_PWR_IND_ON
PCI_EXP_SLTCTL_PWR_IND_BLINK
PCI_EXP_SLTCTL_PWR_IND_OFF
.IP "attn" 12
one of:
PCI_EXP_SLTCTL_ATTN_IND_ON
PCI_EXP_SLTCTL_ATTN_IND_BLINK
PCI_EXP_SLTCTL_ATTN_IND_OFF
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Either \fIpwr\fP or \fIattn\fP can also be INDICATOR_NOOP to leave that indicator
unchanged.
